The paper deals with routing algorithms in geometric structures, specifically convex subdivisions and triangulations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses lower bounds and worst-case analysis, indicating that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The use of randomized algorithms and analysis of their expected performance suggests that the paper may also belong to the network economics (cs.NE) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
